// scenarios/86-jenkins-untrusted-pr-build
// CICD-SEC-4 (Poisoned Pipeline Execution) — Jenkins — CRITICAL
//
// Pattern: the canonical Jenkins "Poisoned Pipeline Execution". A multibranch
// pipeline is configured to BUILD FORK PULL REQUESTS and to TRUST them (the
// GitHub/Bitbucket Branch Source "Discover PRs from forks -> Trust: Everyone"
// strategy). Because the fork's own Jenkinsfile + repo content drive the build,
// an attacker forks, edits the build to dump credentials, opens a PR, and
// Jenkins runs it with the controller's credentials. (OWASP CICD-SEC-4 / Cider
// "PPE".) Jenkins analogue of pull_request_target fork RCE (scenario 01).
//
// The enabling condition is the JOB/folder fork-trust configuration, which
// lives in Jenkins config — NOT in this file. Shown here: a pipeline that runs
// PR-controlled build steps with credentials in scope.
//
// SAFETY: static fixture, nested under scenarios/ (Jenkins runs only a
// configured Jenkinsfile). See README.md.

pipeline {
    agent { label 'build-linux' }
    stages {
        stage('Build PR') {
            steps {
                // DANGER — fork-supplied build runs with controller creds in scope.
                sh 'make build'
                withCredentials([string(credentialsId: 'prod-deploy-token', variable: 'TOKEN')]) {
                    sh './deploy.sh'   // PR-controlled code can read $TOKEN
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
